    "description": "Black-led, queer-inclusive weekly session at Colour Factory in Hackney Wick, running every Monday without fail since 2019. Founded by multi-instrumentalist Neue Grafik (Fred Bwelle), it brings together nu-jazz, neo-soul, hip-hop and R&B in one of London's most genuinely diverse musical spaces. Thundercat once showed up unannounced. The Guardian called it 'the place to experience the raucous edge of London's new jazz scene.'"
