    "description": "The benchmark for London's new jazz scene. South East London collective Steam Down have played every Wednesday at Peckham Levels for over seven years without missing a week. Founded by Saint Lucian-rooted saxophonist Ahnans\u00e9, each session features a rotating cast of London's best musicians journeying through afrobeat, grime, funk and improvised music. The Guardian called it 'the place to experience the raucous edge of London's new jazz scene.' Mixmag: 'Jazz meets grime, afrobeat and funk \u2014 not dissimilar to London raves of the very early 90s.'"
